```bash
#!/bin/bash
set -eux
```

Then create a systemd init script to make sure that runs before microk8s starts, e.g. create `/etc/systemd/system/hfcache.service` with something like:
```
[Unit]
Description=Setup HF cache link
DefaultDependencies=no
Before=microk8s.service
Before=network.target
After=local-fs.target
[Service]
Type=oneshot
RemainAfterExit=yes
ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/setup_hf_cache
[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```
And ensure it's enabled: `systemctl enable hfcache`
